<abstract><t>MPLS-SPRING is an MPLS-based source routing paradigm in which a sender of a packet is allowed to partially or completely specify the route the packet takes through the network by imposing stacked MPLS labels to the packet.  This MPLS -based source routing paradigm could actually be leveraged to realize a unified source routing instruction for both IPv4 and IPv6 underlays.</t></abstract>

